    <briefdescription>
<para>Touch events are a collection of points at a specific moment in time. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>When a multi-touch event occurs, each point represents the points that are currently being touched or the points where a touch has stopped.</para>
<para>The first point is the primary point that&apos;s used for hit-testing. @SINCE_1_9.26 <simplesect kind="note"><para>As this is a handle to an internal object, it should not be copied (or used in a container) as all that will do is copy the handle to the same object. The internal object can change which may not be what an application writer expects. If data does need to be stored in the application, then only the required data should be saved (retrieved using the methods of this class).</para>
</simplesect>
Should not use this in a <ref refid="classDali_1_1TouchEvent" kindref="compound">TouchEvent</ref> container as it is just a handle and the internal object can change. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
